&lt;p&gt;Comments added to solrj/ivy.xml discussing how to choose versions for httpcomponents httpmime and httpcore, based on the httpclient version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ant precommit&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;ant validate-maven-dependencies&lt;/tt&gt; both pass. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All Solr core, solrj, and Solr contrib tests pass, except ChaosMonkeySafeLeaderTest.testDistribSearch, which doesn&apos;t reliably reproduce (sometimes succeeds with a previously failing seed).  It mostly fails for me though (4/5 trials) - it seems to be much slower (~4X) when it fails.  I see Hoss already made an issue for this: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4454&quot; title=&quot;non-reproducible long &amp;quot;stall&amp;quot; running ChaosMonkeySafeLeaderTest.testDistribSearch&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4454&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4454&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committing shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
